Ceria Springwalker/Relationships.summary: Ceria's relationship with Pisces is complex. They first met on the boat to Wistram Academy, where Pisces was one of the few people who was not prejudiced towards Ceria for being a half-Elf.During their time at Wistram, the two grew very close, studying together and helping each other to learn spells. However, the revelation of Pisces' [Necromancer] class alienated Ceria, and she stopped talking to him for some time. Even then, she was still one of the only people in all of Wistram to talk with Pisces. Their relationship would sour when he desecrated Illphres' and several others' bodies by reanimating them to help him raid Archmage Nekhret's tomb and accidentally releasing a swarm of undead guardians. However she argued in Pisces' defense during his trial, though ultimately both were expelled from Wistram, Pisces for his crimes, and Ceria for speaking up for him.

Erin Solstice/Relationships.summary: Erin and Lyonette share a close familial relationship, each being aware of the other's secret identity as anEartherand [Princess] respectively. While Erin is technically the "boss," Lyonette is responsible for the day-to-day management, as well as the technical and business aspects of the inn.

Flos Reimarch/Relationships.summary: There is an implication that Queravia and Flos had a romantic relationship. At the very least he had some kind of special relationship with her.Flos said that he loved talking to her because her company was enjoyable.

Gazi Pathseeker/Relationships.summary: Gazi is completely devoted to him. This is because when she was just a child slave, he had found her at that time, bought her and freed her within a year. He even removed her [Slave] Class, thus giving her a future. Ever since then she has served him.

Ieka Imarris/Relationships.summary: Ieka has a good relationship with her aunt. Valeterisa supported her magical aspirations and helped her take over House Imarris, and Ieka helps smooth over incidents involving her aunt, pays fines for unreturned books, and generally keeps her reputation from being tarnished.

Ishkr Silverfang/Relationships.summary: Liska is Ishkr's more delinquent type sister. She also works in the Wandering Inn alongside him as a Door Gnoll. She is family but he thinks she is too noisy with relationship drama. But he still cares about her, enough to ask Erin for a job for her.

Klbkch/Relationships.summary: Klbkch is Relc's partner, and is the only one able to deal with Relc's personality. Klbkch considers Relc to be his friend, but has no understanding of how they became friends. Despite this, Klbkch would attempt to kill Relc if his Queen ordered it.

Lyonette du Marquin/Relationships.summary: Lyonette begins taking care of Mrsha when Erin was gone from the Inn.Lyonette raises Mrsha as her daughter, and Mrsha accepts Lyonette as her mother. Lyonette is extremely protective of Mrsha, and raises her to the best of her ability.

Montressa du Valeross/Relationships.summary: Montressa likes Erin, despite it all, as she is extraordinary, besides her nature as someone from Earth. She was the most accomplished, highest-level Earthworlder that Montressa knew of, and despite considering Erin insane for making friends with Goblins, Antinium and all the other crazy plans she comes up to, Montressa still respected her because Erin has the same kind of mad genius that some of Wistram’s best [Mages] has.

Ostevien/Relationships.summary: He feels shame for bringing his mother grief, and would rather that she leaves him to his gruesome fate, rather then having her be forced to do as Belavierr wills her, to preserve his live.

Palt Fenrisol/Relationships.summary: Initially, Palt was scared of Erin after he found out that she’d stabbed Beza and nearly killed Isceil with a pot of sauce, because of what they had done to Pisces, and feared that she was going to harm him when she approached him.After he apologized to her by offering her some gifts, and they talked a few times, Erin while she still mistrusted him, would allow him into her Inn.

Pawn/Relationships.summary: When Erin is in Celum, Lyonette is left at the inn to fend for herself, and Pawn is one of the only visitors to give her any attention or help.Pawn helped Lyonette, and Lyonette helped Pawn as well. Lyonette provided meals to Pawn's soldiers during their first excursion above-ground. She and Mrsha also helped Pawn create the first Painted Antinium.Erin would eventually come back, but the two maintained a friendship over time. Lyonette gave Pawn advice on how to lead using her experience as a [Princess].

Pisces Jealnet/Relationships.summary: Pisces' incredibly strict father. A fencer from Terandria that taught the rich scions of nobility how to fence. He had trained Pisces strictly in fencing since he was a child. Pisces seems to have a harsh and physically painful childhood under him teachings and frequently ran away from his classes. He loves necromancy and magic and thus, had always clashed with his father. He hasn't been back since going to Wistram and has no knowledge of how his father is doing. He believes he is alive as he was when he ran away.[citation needed]

Songs.summary: Songsare a function of theSystemthat governsInnworld. They are potentially unique to the bard class.

Synergies.summary: Synergiesare a function of theSystemthat governsInnworld.

Titles.summary: Titlesare a function of theGrand Design of Isthekenousthat was recently unlocked.

Currency.summary: CurrencyinInnworldare coin-based, consisting of copper, silver, and gold pieces. The exchange rate is 10 copper for one silver and 20 silver for one gold.

Book 17/tl;dr.summary: Tyrion Veltras bonds awkwardly with his son Heathon over a tilting lesson. Mrsha has a birthday party, and receives many gifts which make her friends jealous. Ryoka supervises children playing with her wind abilites, chats with Fierre, boxes with Alber, and has a conversation with Farmer Lupp. Ryoka takes a carriage down south towards the High Passes, and gets attacked by the Bloodfeast Raiders.

Book 18/tl;dr.summary: Earthers in Wistram give a presentations and demonstrations, about the shape of both Earth and Innworld, and of combat tactics with an Airsoft gun. The Earthers in Wistram have a therapy session. The archmages spy on the Antinium Hives. Aaron Vanwell (Blackmage) speaks to Amerys in prison. Aaron works with High Mage Telim and the Ullsinoi faction to invent a virtual reality combat game. Wistram issues a broadcast revealing the Golden Triangle as a scam world-wide.

Book 19/tl;dr.summary: Numbtongue makes friends with the patrons of the inn by gambling on card games, and talks with Ratici and Wilovan. Rasea Zecrew tries and fails to recruit a Goblin ship carrying Greydath of Blades to her crew. Rags forms an alliance with an Ogre tribe that's moving to the High Passes. Mavika visits the Goblin Chieftain Anazhure, the [Witch] of the Molten Stone tribe, who is making a deal with another Goblin chieftain.

Book 20/tl;dr.summary: Xrn kidnaps Ryoka to have a conversation. Saliss gets a summons for a military operation, and hides in Erin's inn, talking to Bird, Numbtongue, and Erin, because he doesn't want to go. He's convinced to go anyway by General Shirka, and Chaldion bribes him into the attack on the Hivelands by offering to take six names of Turnscales off wanted lists and redirect the Watch's efforts for three months. Saliss, Mivifa of Feathers (Oteslia's Named Adventurer), Zeter (Manus' Named Adventurer), and a bunch of soldiers attack the Antinium hives and damage the Armored Queen's "Steelclad" project. Saliss fights Wrymvr and Klbktch, finding himself unable to kill Wrymvr. Klbktch gets chopped in half by Wrymvr on purpose, so the Queens can rebuild him. Saliss returns home and announces that he's going to make the antidote for the Strategists.
